  "buggy_files": ["drivers/acpi/video_detect.c"],
  "buggy_functions": ["video_detect_dmi_table"],
  "confidence": 0.85,
  "reasoning": "The Acer TravelMate 5735Z with Intel GM45/GMA 4500MHD chipset is missing from the video_detect_dmi_table. When ACPI backlight type detection runs, the device falls through to auto-detection which defaults to acpi_backlight_video instead of acpi_backlight_native. The ACPI video backlight interface does not work properly on this hardware, but native backlight (from i915 driver) works correctly. The device needs to be added to the DMI table with video_detect_force_native callback to force it to use native backlight. Users can verify this works by booting with acpi_backlight=native parameter, which bypasses auto-detection and uses native backlight directly."
}

